# Charlie community/dev node — environment template.
# Copy the secrets into ~/.claude/channels/discord-charlie/.env (NOT here — this is a
# committed template). The launch script exports the isolation env vars itself.
#
# ~/.claude/channels/discord-charlie/.env should contain:
#   DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=<charlie-bot-token>
#   GITHUB_TOKEN=<fine-grained-PAT-scoped-to-public-repo-fork>   # for PR/code work
#
# Isolation env (set by launch-charlie.sh — shown here for reference):
#   SUTANDO_WORKSPACE=$HOME/.sutando/workspace-charlie
#   SUTANDO_DISCORD_CHANNELS_DIR=$HOME/.claude/channels/discord-charlie
